WEBVTT

00:03.906 --> 00:05.228
I think you all.

00:05.268 --> 00:06.570
I'm so glad to be here with you.

00:07.211 --> 00:12.018
And they asked me if I would kind of go in a certain direction this morning.

00:12.038 --> 00:15.243
And I'm happy to do that because we're going to talk a little bit.

00:15.804 --> 00:20.971
This is not a Christmas message today, although I guess it could be, but we're going to talk about the Holy Spirit today.

00:21.652 --> 00:22.233
Praise the Lord.

00:22.273 --> 00:24.917
And so I want you to just go with me.

00:24.997 --> 00:26.780
We're going to open the Word of God today.

00:26.800 --> 00:33.650
I want you to begin by turning with me to the book of Galatians chapter 3.

00:34.082 --> 00:37.888
And I'm gonna read verse 14, Galatians chapter three, verse 14.

00:37.928 --> 00:50.968
And I want you to listen carefully to what we're saying today, because it's not just a Bible study, we're going to practice the word, because when I get through, we're gonna pray for people to be filled with the Holy Spirit.

00:51.990 --> 00:53.332
Thank you for your enthusiasm.

00:53.853 --> 00:56.096
Sound man, can you turn their volume up a little bit?

00:56.116 --> 00:56.777
I'm not hearing that.

00:57.058 --> 00:59.922
I said, we're gonna pray for people to be filled with the Spirit.

01:00.994 --> 01:03.638
Before we begin, I'd like just to pray.

01:03.718 --> 01:07.063
Father, we thank you for the word of God.

01:07.864 --> 01:11.710
You have exalted your word even above your name.

01:12.331 --> 01:16.157
We thank you today for the blessing of the Holy Spirit.

01:16.477 --> 01:23.988
We thank you for that anointing which we have received from you that abides in us and teaches us all things.

01:24.429 --> 01:30.578
I pray today you would open the eyes of our hearts to see truth more clearly.

01:30.946 --> 01:38.515
to walk in it more accurately, to be not forgetful hearers, but practitioners of your word.

01:39.196 --> 01:49.367
And we thank you, Father, because we believe that your word will never return to you void, but it shall accomplish that which you please and prosper in the thing for which you sent it.

01:49.708 --> 01:57.076
And we give you honor in advance and thanks for every life that is touched and changed in the name of Jesus.

01:57.116 --> 01:58.738
Can someone say amen?

01:59.586 --> 02:02.190
Sound man, can you turn my bottom up just a little bit, please?

02:02.230 --> 02:02.631
Thank you.

02:03.011 --> 02:06.516
So I want to read to you Galatians chapter three and verse 14.

02:07.798 --> 02:23.141
It says, so that in Christ Jesus, the blessing of Abraham might come to the Gentiles so that we might receive the promised spirit through faith.

02:25.104 --> 02:28.850
So Christ redeemed us by dying on the cross.

02:29.538 --> 02:39.429
He brought us out from under the law so that Abraham's blessing might be ours to have and to hold.

02:41.231 --> 02:54.386
But he also ransomed us and purchased our freedom so that we could receive the promised Holy Spirit.

02:56.162 --> 03:00.827
I think many times we read that verse, we read the first part and we skip over the second part.

03:01.909 --> 03:17.246
So although it is the Holy Spirit who imparts to us eternal life and who comes to dwell inside of our hearts at the moment of conversion when we're born again.

03:17.286 --> 03:23.794
However, when the New Testament speaks of the promised

03:23.938 --> 03:42.399
Holy Spirit or the promise of the Spirit, it is specifically referring to an experience that is separate and subsequent to salvation, meaning it's not salvation, it's something that comes after salvation, the baptism with the Holy Spirit.

03:43.520 --> 03:48.626
So Christ redeemed us so that we could be baptized with the Holy Spirit.

03:49.378 --> 03:50.199
Are you out there today?

03:50.700 --> 03:53.123
And notice this verse again, there's a reason why I read this.

03:53.604 --> 03:59.411
It says, so that we might receive the promised spirit through faith.

04:01.935 --> 04:06.962
Now over the years, Sister Yen mentioned that my ministry is based in India.

04:06.982 --> 04:15.213
I've lived there for 30 years and pastor church and we have four branch churches and a Bible school and over and special meetings.

04:15.273 --> 04:19.218
And over the years, I suppose that I have prayed for hundreds

04:19.874 --> 04:24.281
I don't know, maybe, maybe thousands of people to be baptized with the Holy Spirit.

04:25.442 --> 04:43.570
And I have observed in my experience, my very limited experience, of course, but I have observed that the main reason why Christians fail to receive the infilling of the Spirit to receive the gift of the Holy Spirit is a lack of faith.

04:44.866 --> 04:45.166
Let's see.

04:45.467 --> 04:47.009
That reminds me of many scriptures.

04:47.049 --> 04:49.272
For example, James chapter one verse six.

04:49.292 --> 04:58.483
And I know that for many of you, you know, this, this is nothing new at all, but, but I think there are other folks that maybe need to hear this or maybe it needs to be reinforced.

04:58.744 --> 05:06.834
For example, in James chapter one verse six, we read, but let him ask in faith with no doubting.

05:08.194 --> 05:13.440
but let him ask in faith, so I was telling you how to pray, let him ask in faith with no doubting.

05:13.960 --> 05:31.660
So the Greek literally says, because the New Testament was originally written in Greek, the Greek literally says without a single doubt, actually looked it up last night because I want to make sure, without a single doubt or without any hesitation, you see.

05:32.261 --> 05:36.626
So then James goes on to say in the next verse, verse seven,

05:36.706 --> 05:45.220
that the person who doubts should not expect to receive anything from the Lord.

05:45.801 --> 05:49.267
Well, anything would include the gift of the Holy Spirit.

05:49.567 --> 05:54.155
And again, I'm not talking about salvation, I'm talking about the baptism with the Holy Spirit.

05:55.017 --> 06:03.090
So often the problem is this, that we do a lot of asking, but not a lot of believing.

06:05.634 --> 06:10.641
This is especially true in some circles and some churches and some denominations.

06:10.701 --> 06:14.106
They'll pray all night long to be filled with the Spirit.

06:16.008 --> 06:25.341
And they'll sometimes be praying over a period of days and fasting and crying and repenting and a lot of things.

06:26.382 --> 06:31.890
But he says here that we might receive the promised Holy Spirit through faith.

06:32.482 --> 06:54.375
I like something Smith Wigglesworth said, and I guess it's just a habit of mine that I have to say something about Smith Wigglesworth almost in every sermon, but he said, I can get more out of God or from God by believing Him for one minute than I can by shouting at Him all night long.

06:57.140 --> 06:57.740
Let me say that again.

06:57.760 --> 07:01.426
I can get more from God by believing Him for one minute

07:02.082 --> 07:04.526
that can't vice shouting at him all night long.

07:04.546 --> 07:05.607
Well, let me ask you this question.

07:05.908 --> 07:09.473
Did you have to pray all night long to be saved?

07:11.296 --> 07:15.583
I mean, maybe that's your testimony, but you didn't have to pray all night long.

07:15.803 --> 07:24.136
It doesn't take 12 hours to get saved when you have the right information and the right attitude and response of that information.

07:24.697 --> 07:30.546
So that tells me that James chapter one verse six and seven indicates, and this is important,

07:30.818 --> 07:40.952
that indicates that even a single doubt can nullify or undo your prayer.

07:43.175 --> 07:53.068
So I think a lot of times we pray and everything is fine and everything is scriptural, everything is biblical, and then we entertain a single doubt.

07:54.811 --> 08:00.338
And that's enough to just cancel everything we said.

08:00.546 --> 08:04.772
Of course, in this building, there's all kinds of wires from the video camera and the lights.

08:05.292 --> 08:11.901
Well, a single cut to a wire is enough to stop the flow of electricity.

08:12.702 --> 08:14.985
You don't have to blow up the whole building.

08:15.005 --> 08:17.608
Just a single cut is enough to do it.

08:17.949 --> 08:20.012
So doubt disconnects us.

08:21.574 --> 08:24.978
Doubt disconnects us.

08:25.346 --> 08:28.171
At my home, I have a home here in Virginia Beach.

08:28.211 --> 08:29.734
This is actually where I'm from originally.

08:30.055 --> 08:37.369
So in my home, I have an electric guitar and an amplifier and cables and several effects pedals.

08:37.830 --> 08:45.965
So if I plug it all in and I don't get any sound, I don't immediately go to the phone and complain to dominion power.

08:47.488 --> 08:48.370
Something's wrong.

08:48.738 --> 08:52.462
Need to check that nuclear power plant you've got over there in Surrey.

08:52.483 --> 08:54.024
No, no, no, no, no.

08:54.185 --> 08:58.109
I check there's a loose connection somewhere, right?

08:58.890 --> 09:05.418
So before you complain to God about his lack of power, you need to troubleshoot your prayers.

09:06.800 --> 09:08.241
Let me just help you out a little bit.

09:09.483 --> 09:11.986
If there's a problem, it's not up there, it's down here.

09:15.871 --> 09:18.674
Sometimes people, they say things like,

09:18.850 --> 09:20.633
I don't understand the Lord.

09:21.274 --> 09:24.479
Just seems to me that sometimes he's not really paying attention.

09:24.539 --> 09:26.902
So you're accusing God of wrongdoing.

09:28.845 --> 09:29.827
And that's no small thing.

09:30.408 --> 09:31.810
Now, there's a mistake that's made.

09:31.890 --> 09:32.591
It's down here.

09:32.611 --> 09:37.478
It doesn't mean you're some terrible person, but it does mean that there's somewhere there's a disconnection.

09:38.700 --> 09:39.361
So what do you do?

09:40.022 --> 09:42.226
Just cry and weep and moan and grow.

09:42.666 --> 09:44.089
No, you fix it.

09:45.491 --> 09:46.392
Amen.

09:46.412 --> 09:47.634
So to doubt

09:48.322 --> 09:53.991
Doesn't mean that you totally reject God's word, that you just walk away from it.

09:54.632 --> 10:12.879
No, it means to waver slightly, to question inwardly, even for a moment, to wonder, well, I wonder, that's called doubt, right?

10:12.899 --> 10:17.426
To hesitate, or to be less than fully persuaded,

10:18.562 --> 10:21.767
There's a lot more doubt in us than we realize.

10:22.668 --> 10:25.913
Look at your neighbor and say it's time for the doubt to get out.

10:28.257 --> 10:29.679
Smile when you say that.

10:32.704 --> 10:46.866
So many years ago in our church in Northeast India, I preached on a Sunday morning similar to today, and afterward I gave an invitation

10:47.010 --> 10:49.293
for people to be filled with the Holy Spirit.

10:49.573 --> 10:56.923
Again, I'm not talking about salvation, I understand it's the Spirit of God that gives us new life, but I'm talking about being baptized with the Holy Spirit.

10:57.344 --> 11:01.128
And several people came forward, including one older woman.

11:02.670 --> 11:07.577
And I prayed for them, and when I laid hands on her, she did not receive.

11:08.298 --> 11:09.099
Nothing happened.

11:09.980 --> 11:14.546
And I had a sense in my heart that it's because she was not really sure

11:15.202 --> 11:18.806
if this is for her, if this is really of God, et cetera.

11:19.507 --> 11:24.573
Well, you see, the thing is people think, I'll let him pray for me.

11:25.394 --> 11:27.317
And if it's of God, I'll get it.

11:28.338 --> 11:29.960
If it's God's will, it will happen.

11:30.741 --> 11:36.428
And if it doesn't, then I guess maybe for some reason it wasn't for me or it wasn't God's will.

11:36.808 --> 11:43.376
Well, again, you know, what if a sinner came to their altar call and said, well, I'll let them pray for me to get saved.

11:43.437 --> 11:44.658
And if it's God's will,

11:44.770 --> 11:45.591
then I'll get saved.

11:45.611 --> 11:47.673
And if it's not, then I guess I'll go to hell.

11:48.454 --> 11:50.075
No, no, that's not scriptural.

11:50.676 --> 11:51.557
That's not scriptural.

11:51.817 --> 11:52.898
We receive by faith.

11:52.918 --> 11:54.420
That means you're sure.

11:54.540 --> 11:59.525
Faith is being sure of what you hope for when you say, well, that means you're not sure.

12:02.047 --> 12:02.788
So that's not faith.

12:04.530 --> 12:08.494
So you don't pray and then wait till it happens and then believe.

12:09.695 --> 12:12.658
No, no, you come believing, knowing what's going to happen.

12:14.306 --> 12:14.546
Right.

12:15.027 --> 12:19.175
So the next Sunday, uh, kind of the same thing.

12:19.796 --> 12:21.980
I preached and then I gave an invitation.

12:22.040 --> 12:26.709
We sometimes say an altar call and several people came forward, including the same woman.

12:27.310 --> 12:27.531
Right.

12:28.432 --> 12:30.857
And so I was giving them some instructions.

12:30.937 --> 12:34.965
Pastor David, you know, the kind of thing you say, I'm going to pray for him to lay hands on you, blah, blah, blah.

12:34.985 --> 12:37.810
And you could tell she's just full of anticipation.

12:38.434 --> 12:41.578
She's practically, she's kind of like bouncing up and down a little bit.

12:41.879 --> 12:47.827
Her attitude, her posture, everything seems to indicate like, come on, come on, come on, come on.

12:47.847 --> 12:50.010
You know, let's get through all this time.

12:50.110 --> 12:50.711
I'm ready now.

12:52.794 --> 12:54.196
See, there was different attitude.

12:54.837 --> 12:56.439
Faith is an attitude of the heart.

12:57.821 --> 12:59.824
It's not just theology on paper.

13:00.044 --> 13:01.426
It's an attitude of the heart.

13:01.826 --> 13:09.273
All right, some people say we believe this and this and this, this is our tenants of faith, but they don't actually believe nothing.

13:09.293 --> 13:17.982
So when I came to her, I think I may have gone to her first, I don't remember, but when I came to her, as soon as I touched her, bam, she started speaking in other tongues.

13:18.802 --> 13:20.804
Another woman was from a Roman Catholic background.

13:21.725 --> 13:30.834
She was at that point, you know, I don't know how old she was, she didn't tell me, but I think she was approaching maybe halfway to 70 or more,

13:31.330 --> 13:38.218
And, you know, she didn't have a Pentecostal background, a word of faith background.

13:38.839 --> 13:42.383
That don't matter that we might receive by faith.

13:43.164 --> 13:43.925
Are you out there today?

13:44.465 --> 13:45.026
Praise the Lord.

13:45.486 --> 13:45.847
Amen.

13:46.227 --> 13:46.948
Glory to God.

13:46.968 --> 13:48.450
Now, notice the scripture with me.

13:48.931 --> 13:50.632
Romans chapter 10, verse 14.

13:50.673 --> 13:53.976
And while I'm speaking, if you feel like smiling, go ahead.

13:53.996 --> 13:55.378
I don't mind.

13:57.666 --> 13:59.529
I know it takes a little bit of effort there.

13:59.549 --> 14:01.532
When you smile, you increase your face value.

14:04.015 --> 14:07.741
And Romans chapter, we should put a mirror back here so you can see what I see.

14:08.001 --> 14:10.865
Now in Romans, you might scare yourself.

14:11.206 --> 14:21.722
In Romans chapter 10, verse 14, we read the scripture, and how are they to believe in Him of whom they have never heard?

14:23.865 --> 14:24.786
You can't believe.

14:25.282 --> 14:26.644
if you don't know anything about it.

14:26.965 --> 14:28.407
So that's true.

14:28.487 --> 14:31.953
That verse is true concerning faith in Christ for salvation.

14:32.213 --> 14:33.315
That's actually what he's talking about.

14:33.956 --> 14:36.700
But it's also true concerning the Holy Spirit.

14:38.103 --> 14:44.233
See, we can't have faith to be filled just because we want to be filled.

14:47.678 --> 14:48.319
That's not enough.

14:49.401 --> 14:52.626
Just because you want something doesn't mean you have faith for it.

14:53.698 --> 14:56.361
How many of you would like to have a billion dollars raise your hand?

14:57.182 --> 14:58.283
How many of you have faith for it?

14:59.384 --> 15:01.166
Well, if you did, you'd have it.

15:04.650 --> 15:07.133
And if you do have it, please meet me after the service.

15:07.153 --> 15:08.735
I want to especially pray for you.

15:08.795 --> 15:12.339
That's the secret.

15:12.759 --> 15:19.106
And so you can't believe something if you don't know what the Bible says about it, right?

15:19.487 --> 15:22.290
So many people, they are sincere.

15:22.402 --> 15:30.274
They are genuine, they're earnest, they love God, but many people are operating on incomplete information.

15:32.057 --> 15:43.154
And I think what happens is this, we kind of assimilate into the church culture, but that doesn't mean we're really grounded in his word.

15:44.834 --> 15:50.843
You come, you know when to stand up, you know when to sit down, you know the words of the songs.

15:50.903 --> 15:52.065
If you don't, it's on the screen.

15:52.405 --> 15:56.912
You know how to say amen.

15:56.952 --> 15:58.475
And you know when to lift your hand.

15:58.535 --> 16:00.217
And you know the style.

16:02.240 --> 16:05.085
But you may not know the substance.

16:05.105 --> 16:06.567
So your shout has no clout.

16:08.069 --> 16:11.314
You don't know why you're saying what you're saying, right?

16:11.490 --> 16:38.087
And really that happens I think in every church it definitely happens in my experience there in Northeast India So we need to we need to and then some people It's worse They're working they're operating with misinformation And because they've been told that that speaking in tongues that's of the devil it is yes And so if you've been mentioned the word tongues they freak out Praise the Lord.

16:38.368 --> 16:39.890
So it's harder

16:40.418 --> 16:42.621
to unlearn than it is to learn.

16:44.444 --> 16:48.269
It's harder to remove wrong teaching than it is to learn right teaching.

16:48.309 --> 16:53.957
That's why actually people that don't know nothing are actually fairly easy to get filled.

16:55.619 --> 16:58.343
See, I was raised Presbyterian, God's frozen people.

16:58.744 --> 17:00.306
They didn't tell us anything.

17:00.610 --> 17:02.472
So I was easy to get filled.

17:02.733 --> 17:03.754
I was easy to receive.

17:04.175 --> 17:09.262
But in Nagaland in Northeast India, some of them have been taught all kinds of things.

17:09.642 --> 17:14.328
And so if you mentioned salvation, they tear up and say, amen, that's right.

17:14.368 --> 17:16.491
They all believe in salvation, but none of them are saved.

17:16.772 --> 17:21.198
But if you talk about the baptism with the Holy Spirit, they look at you kind of funny.

17:24.742 --> 17:30.450
I mean, you can say amen, but we can look at your faith, face and see your faith.

17:35.074 --> 17:41.063
So it took a lot, a lot, a long time and a lot of teaching until people started being filled.

17:41.083 --> 17:44.127
So let's take a look at some scriptures in the time that we have this morning.

17:45.449 --> 17:58.909
So the same day that Jesus was raised from the dead, that first resurrection Sunday, at evening, he appeared to his disciples in that upper room.

18:00.171 --> 18:04.978
And something rather interesting, John tells us in John chapter 20, verse 22,

18:05.410 --> 18:11.499
It says, he breathed on them and said, receive the Holy Spirit.

18:13.442 --> 18:14.624
That's kind of peculiar, isn't it?

18:14.684 --> 18:18.631
He didn't say, he didn't just say, I want to pray for you, I want to lay hands on you.

18:18.811 --> 18:22.036
He breathed on them and said, receive the Holy Spirit.

18:22.096 --> 18:28.125
Now, again, in the original language, it says, he breathed into them.

18:29.207 --> 18:31.571
I think the word is infosau, something like that.

18:31.991 --> 18:33.714
And the same word was used to describe

18:33.858 --> 18:35.741
a man in Greece playing a flute?

18:36.622 --> 18:40.107
Well, he doesn't blow on like the flute or the pipe.

18:40.467 --> 18:43.612
He blows air inside of it, through it, see?

18:44.133 --> 18:51.683
So Jesus did to his disciples in that upper room what God the Father did to Adam in the garden.

18:53.286 --> 18:55.970
He breathed into them the breath of life.

18:56.931 --> 18:59.054
You see, this is when they were born again.

18:59.114 --> 19:01.257
Now, you might say, well, wait a minute.

19:01.297 --> 19:01.938
Wait a minute.

19:02.434 --> 19:05.160
I mean, weren't they born again all those three and a half years?

19:05.200 --> 19:07.465
They accompanied Jesus?

19:07.485 --> 19:07.686
No.

19:08.648 --> 19:09.470
Nope.

19:09.550 --> 19:10.672
They believed in Him.

19:10.732 --> 19:20.434
They were followers of Him, but they were still living under the old covenant because Jesus inaugurated the new covenant with His blood when He went into the heavenly

19:20.482 --> 19:21.303
Holy of holies.

19:21.724 --> 19:27.271
Nobody could receive eternal life until after Jesus was raised from the dead.

19:27.492 --> 19:37.546
What does Romans chapter 10 verse 9 say that if you confess with your mouth Jesus as Lord and believe in your heart that God has raised him from the dead you will be saved.

19:37.566 --> 19:42.332
Well they called him Lord but they couldn't believe he was raised from the dead until after it happened.

19:43.574 --> 19:45.276
In fact initially they didn't believe it.

19:46.718 --> 19:47.299
Are you listening to me?

19:48.200 --> 19:49.522
Praise the Lord.

19:49.794 --> 19:52.879
He breathed on them, breathed into them and said, received the Holy Spirit.

19:53.000 --> 20:13.074
Now, if this verse in John 22, if this verse was the only verse we had on the subject, then we might assume that, you know, if you're born again, you have the Holy Spirit in you, and that's all of the Holy Spirit there is to have, end of story, case closed.

20:14.722 --> 20:19.568
but this is not the only verse that we have on the subject.

20:19.988 --> 20:28.519
Again, this is a problem sometimes people take like one little verse to the exclusion of other verses on the same subject.

20:28.559 --> 20:41.795
Don't just base your whole doctrine and theology on one verse or a part of verse, see everything the Bible has to say on the subject, then you have a more complete understanding of what God is trying to tell you, right?

20:42.416 --> 20:44.018
So it's interesting

20:44.994 --> 20:59.233
Before going to the cross earlier than John 2022, before going to the cross, Jesus told his disciples this in John chapter 16 and verse seven, John chapter 16, verse seven.

20:59.874 --> 21:04.400
Nevertheless, I tell you the truth, it is to your advantage that I go away.

21:05.121 --> 21:06.723
We could stop there and preach another sermon.

21:08.025 --> 21:12.050
Some of us dream that we were there walking with him through Galilee.

21:12.418 --> 21:14.140
and through the streets of Jerusalem.

21:14.360 --> 21:17.244
But he says, actually, it's better that that didn't happen to you.

21:19.446 --> 21:19.727
Why?

21:20.808 --> 21:26.635
For if I do not go away, the helper, the comforter, will not come to you.

21:27.415 --> 21:29.658
But if I go, I will send him to you.

21:29.678 --> 21:35.885
That means it's better for you to have the Holy Spirit than to be physically present when Jesus walked the earth.

21:36.786 --> 21:39.890
See, they were spectators, but they were not participants.

21:40.994 --> 21:43.138
They saw him, but they were not like him.

21:44.039 --> 21:44.760
Are you listening to me?

21:45.121 --> 21:48.346
So the helper in this verse, the comforter is the Holy Spirit.

21:48.827 --> 21:49.929
So let me ask you a question.

21:50.390 --> 21:50.931
Think about this.

21:52.513 --> 22:04.754
So if a church, a pastor in Northeast India, if a church member contacts me there in India and says, I'm sick and I say, all right.

22:05.314 --> 22:13.222
Um, you know, maybe I'm busy today or something, but I can't go, but I will send the associate pastor to visit you.

22:14.884 --> 22:22.511
Wouldn't the church member understand that I will not be personally present at that meeting?

22:25.494 --> 22:28.958
You know, I'm sending, okay, I hear you sister Zama Zama.

22:28.978 --> 22:33.042
So I'm sending the assistant pastor, associate pastor to visit you.

22:33.474 --> 22:37.459
And she would understand that pastor John is not going to come, but someone else will come.

22:37.499 --> 22:38.901
He's sending someone else.

22:39.581 --> 22:41.364
I'll see if I said, okay, I'm coming.

22:41.424 --> 22:49.033
And by the way, I'm bringing the associate, associate pastor with me, then she would understand we're both going to be coming together at the same time.

22:50.295 --> 22:56.642
In John chapter 20, he was physically present.

22:56.662 --> 22:57.824
He didn't send anything.

22:59.986 --> 23:02.930
And yet he said, if I go, I will send him to you.

23:04.002 --> 23:08.029
So he couldn't be talking about what happened in John chapter 20 verse 22.

23:08.089 --> 23:09.391
That doesn't fit.

23:10.553 --> 23:12.416
That doesn't agree with what he said earlier.

23:13.658 --> 23:24.876
See, however, after that first resurrection Sunday, several days later, maybe, maybe closer to 40 days later, he said something else to them.

23:25.076 --> 23:31.186
Before he just went up to heaven, he said in Luke chapter 24 verse 49, behold,

23:31.650 --> 23:36.055
I'm sending the promise of my father upon you."

23:36.075 --> 23:39.759
So that means when he spoke those words, it had not happened yet.

23:40.560 --> 23:43.904
Yet he's already breathed into them the breath of life.

23:45.666 --> 23:50.171
See, I'm sending the promise of my father upon you.

23:50.712 --> 23:52.994
Notice he didn't say in you, he said, upon you.

23:54.016 --> 23:59.602
But stay in the city until you are clothed with power from on high.

24:00.034 --> 24:02.857
What is the promise of the father that he's referring to?

24:03.458 --> 24:04.339
It's the Holy Spirit.

24:04.359 --> 24:06.442
It's the Holy Spirit.

24:07.463 --> 24:17.015
So again, many churches leave the impression that after you get saved, you should immediately go out there and win the lost.

24:17.035 --> 24:21.520
But before Jesus told his disciples to go, he told them to stay.

24:23.843 --> 24:26.386
Before starting, he told them to wait.

24:26.946 --> 24:27.887
Are you out there today?

24:27.927 --> 24:35.136
Now Luke is also the author or the instrument that God used to write the book of Acts, right?

24:35.396 --> 24:39.682
So we've seen a very similar statement in Acts chapter one, verse four and five.

24:40.242 --> 24:56.242
Acts chapter one, verse four says this, and while staying with them, this is after his resurrection, while staying with them, he ordered them not to depart from Jerusalem, but wait for the promise of the father.

24:56.834 --> 24:58.417
which he said, you heard from me.

24:59.039 --> 25:05.332
Now, there are many promises from God, the Father, we have a Bible full of promises, which one is he referring to?

25:05.813 --> 25:17.458
He went on to say, notice verse five, for John baptized with water, but you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit, not many days from now.

25:17.954 --> 25:22.720
Now, this is after he's already breathed into them and said, receive the Holy Spirit.

25:23.120 --> 25:25.744
So that means this has not yet happened to them.

25:26.044 --> 25:28.047
There's something more than just salvation.

25:29.909 --> 25:32.832
Now, when we baptize someone in water, what do we do?

25:32.872 --> 25:38.920
Do we hand that person a glass and say, drink this in the name of the Father, Son and Holy Spirit?

25:38.960 --> 25:40.562
No, I mean,

25:40.706 --> 25:44.252
I don't think that's what we do here, right?

25:44.332 --> 25:52.264
I'm just guessing, you know, because again, the Greek word baptizo means to immerse, to submerge, right?

25:52.344 --> 26:01.639
In fact, the same Greek word was used to describe in secular writings, not the Bible, a ship that sank to the bottom of the sea, it went down, right?

26:02.420 --> 26:09.010
So when we baptize a person in water, I mean, you know, he's completely covered in water, you know,

26:09.282 --> 26:10.284
It's not possible.

26:13.088 --> 26:16.114
Sometimes they kind of want to be baptized, but I don't want to get wet.

26:18.999 --> 26:20.381
Not sure how we're going to do that, sister.

26:22.745 --> 26:28.114
You can bring a change of clothes or something, and sometimes people

26:28.322 --> 26:35.855
Water baptism doesn't save you, but we're saved by faith, but water baptism should be a test and a testimony of your faith, you see.

26:36.296 --> 26:46.754
But, you know, sometimes people, when you water baptize them, they're kind of struggling, the water's cold, or, you know, they feel a little frayed, and, you know, and then sometimes pastors think, like, you know, this rascal, I'm gonna hold him down a little longer.

26:46.814 --> 26:49.619
Wait till the air bubbles come up.

26:51.463 --> 26:53.426
But that's not true, yeah, that isn't true.

26:53.634 --> 26:58.278
So a person comes up, water baptized, they are dripping wet.

26:59.279 --> 27:00.360
They're soaked to the bone.

27:01.802 --> 27:05.845
God wants you to be completely covered with the Holy Spirit.

27:06.146 --> 27:09.109
He wants you to be dripping with the Holy Spirit.

27:09.409 --> 27:10.870
He doesn't want you just to have a sip.

27:11.311 --> 27:13.993
He wants to have rivers flowing out from you.

27:14.033 --> 27:15.034
Can I get an amen?

27:15.795 --> 27:18.617
So again, let's talk about Smith Wigglesworth one more time.

27:18.678 --> 27:23.442
He said this, a man may be saved and he may be sanctified

27:23.554 --> 27:27.701
but he will never be satisfied until he is filled with the Holy Spirit.

27:29.464 --> 27:34.952
Now, some Christians, some church people, not you, but maybe they're church down the street.

27:34.972 --> 27:41.803
Some church people have this sort of disdain for the expression baptism with the Holy Spirit.

27:41.823 --> 27:48.434
When you say that, their facial expression is one of a little bit mild contempt.

27:50.594 --> 27:52.657
And we don't use that expression in my church.

27:52.717 --> 27:55.281
Well, we're not in your church.

27:55.301 --> 27:57.264
But Jesus used this expression.

27:59.367 --> 28:01.150
Jesus used these words.

28:01.170 --> 28:05.316
So is it okay to quote Jesus or do I have to get your permission first?

28:08.822 --> 28:09.042
Right.

28:09.343 --> 28:11.686
And not only that, so did John the Baptist.

28:12.087 --> 28:18.096
For example, Matthew chapter three, verse 11, Matthew three, 11, John the Baptist is speaking.

28:18.957 --> 28:19.538
So, so

28:19.650 --> 28:21.813
Anybody here came from a Baptist background?

28:22.875 --> 28:23.195
Anybody?

28:23.255 --> 28:23.916
There's a hand.

28:23.996 --> 28:24.557
Anybody else?

28:24.617 --> 28:25.258
It's not an ultracol.

28:25.278 --> 28:26.139
I'm just asking a question.

28:27.040 --> 28:27.581
So all right.

28:27.601 --> 28:29.864
So why don't we listen to the first Baptist?

28:31.507 --> 28:31.867
John.

28:32.428 --> 28:33.189
He's so Baptist.

28:33.269 --> 28:34.010
It's his last name.

28:35.012 --> 28:35.953
John the Baptist.

28:36.373 --> 28:48.210
He said this, I baptize you with water for repentance, but he who was coming after me is mightier than I, who sandals, I'm not worthy to carry.

28:48.738 --> 28:52.664
He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and fire.

28:53.866 --> 28:54.967
Isn't that amazing?

28:55.768 --> 29:01.797
You know, some Baptist folks, bless my wife was Baptist, my mother was Baptist, so I don't have anything against the Baptist.

29:01.817 --> 29:04.862
Don't misunderstand me, the two women who love me the most were Baptist.

29:04.882 --> 29:10.070
But, you know, some Baptists, they get a little uneasy, talk about the Baptist's Holy Spirit, they back off.

29:11.071 --> 29:13.655
This is the message John the Baptist preached.

29:13.675 --> 29:18.322
In fact, this statement, a very similar statement is found in all four gospels.

29:18.978 --> 29:22.083
Now see, not all four gospels record the same miracles.

29:22.603 --> 29:24.506
John records some things, the others don't.

29:25.007 --> 29:31.597
Sometimes Matthew and Luke record something that Mark didn't, but here all four tell us the same thing.

29:32.919 --> 29:33.980
He's coming after me.

29:34.241 --> 29:37.345
He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.

29:38.808 --> 29:39.809
So let me ask you a question.

29:40.810 --> 29:41.512
Which is greater?

29:42.693 --> 29:43.414
Which is greater?

29:44.135 --> 29:48.562
John the Baptist or Jesus the baptizer?

29:51.042 --> 29:51.763
Which is greater?

29:51.783 --> 29:54.185
Water or fire?

29:57.568 --> 30:00.611
In this sense that the water baptism is a symbol.

30:00.851 --> 30:01.412
It's right.

30:01.512 --> 30:02.553
It's a commandment of the Lord.

30:03.193 --> 30:05.596
But this is not some symbolic thing.

30:06.276 --> 30:07.558
This is actual.

30:08.739 --> 30:09.780
This is reality.

30:10.200 --> 30:14.364
This is being filled with a person, the Holy Spirit.

30:14.664 --> 30:15.625
Can I get any amen?

30:17.687 --> 30:20.690
So years ago, and maybe this will help somebody,

30:21.250 --> 30:28.082
Years ago, I was invited to speak at a large conference in Nagaland in Northeast India.

30:29.163 --> 30:32.850
And I was going to speak in the afternoon to this large crowd.

30:33.771 --> 30:41.504
And as I was leaving my room, like this guest house, in fact, I had my hand on the doorknob because I remember exactly where I was when this happened.

30:41.524 --> 30:42.005
It's so funny.

30:42.266 --> 30:45.171
I couldn't tell you the date, but I know exactly where I was.

30:45.571 --> 30:47.154
Suddenly the Lord spoke to my heart.

30:48.130 --> 30:51.794
And sometimes I don't know why at a particular time or something this would happen.

30:52.035 --> 31:01.406
But the Lord spoke to my heart and He said, John, remember this, I am the baptizer with the Holy Spirit, not you.

31:03.389 --> 31:05.531
And I thought that was funny that He would say that, you know.

31:06.332 --> 31:09.436
Well, when I got to the meeting, I found out why.

31:11.839 --> 31:14.322
Because nobody received nothing.

31:15.682 --> 31:18.105
They stared at me like they were a photograph.

31:18.186 --> 31:22.612
I mean, some of them, they didn't even look like cadavers.

31:22.672 --> 31:24.975
I mean, they just didn't move.

31:25.796 --> 31:30.683
I thought I was speaking to the People's Republic of China Communist Party leadership meeting or something like that.

31:30.923 --> 31:32.626
They did not look like believers to me.

31:32.906 --> 31:36.031
And they just stared at me and grimaced.

31:36.051 --> 31:38.013
And I have to tell you something kind of interesting.

31:38.294 --> 31:44.082
You can't always go by that because in Northeast India, they're very poker faced in church.

31:45.506 --> 31:48.669
What I mean by that, maybe that's not appropriate analogy for church.

31:48.709 --> 31:50.671
But what I mean by that is they show no expression.

31:51.192 --> 31:52.172
You don't know what they're thinking.

31:52.253 --> 31:59.560
One time in our church, there was a man sitting near the front and he just grimaced at me the whole service.

32:00.561 --> 32:03.744
When I looked over at his way, he snarled.

32:04.885 --> 32:06.586
His nostrils flared.

32:06.606 --> 32:08.769
It seemed like he was going to bite me.

32:08.809 --> 32:12.492
In fact, as I looked at him, I got a little irritated.

32:12.612 --> 32:14.354
Did you ever get irritated?

32:14.594 --> 32:15.835
Well, you don't have to tell me about we know.

32:18.358 --> 32:20.060
You know, and I thought, what's what's your problem?

32:20.080 --> 32:20.741
What's your problem?

32:21.021 --> 32:28.950
You know, I felt like walking right over there and slap him a couple of times and go back to the pulpit, you know, when the service dismissed, he walked right to me.

32:29.871 --> 32:35.297
I mean, so as soon as I said, Amen, you know, you go home, he came made a beeline right for me.

32:35.317 --> 32:36.478
And I thought, okay, here we go.

32:36.798 --> 32:37.259
Here we go.

32:38.620 --> 32:39.281
Bring it on.

32:39.361 --> 32:40.082
Bring it on.

32:40.802 --> 32:44.087
And he said to me, they have a tendency to speak real rough.

32:44.107 --> 32:44.708
It's kind of funny.

32:45.069 --> 32:47.713
He said, Mr. John, he's calling me Mr. John.

32:47.753 --> 32:49.736
Mr. John, I want to tell you something.

32:50.697 --> 32:51.458
I want to tell you something.

32:51.478 --> 32:56.907
And I said, yes, he said, that was the best sermon I have ever heard in my life.

33:00.853 --> 33:04.338
I hate to see what you look like when it's a bad sermon, if that's what you look like.

33:04.610 --> 33:09.135
I guess he was processing it, he was thinking it, so you can't always tell, right?

33:09.476 --> 33:10.357
What people are thinking.

33:10.377 --> 33:15.903
My wife helped me in this regard because, as I said, they're very poker faced in church.

33:15.943 --> 33:17.965
It's been a major thing to deal with.

33:18.746 --> 33:23.792
And see, like my wife said, if you say something in church and everybody says, amen.

33:23.852 --> 33:28.237
That means they knew that and believed it before you said it.

33:30.820 --> 33:32.722
But if you say something and they're just quiet,

33:33.090 --> 33:35.073
That means maybe they're processing it.

33:35.815 --> 33:37.017
They've never heard that before.

33:37.337 --> 33:39.621
They're thinking about it or they're asleep.

33:40.803 --> 33:41.264
Could be both.

33:43.327 --> 33:43.949
Praise the Lord.

33:44.269 --> 33:44.590
Amen.

33:45.311 --> 33:50.259
So, you know, Jesus is the baptized or the Holy Spirit, not me, not you.

33:50.279 --> 33:56.530
So what am I saying is if we, if we pray for people, minister to people and they don't receive, it doesn't mean we're a failure.

33:58.562 --> 34:01.707
And we shouldn't feel like, well, I'm never gonna pray for anybody again.

34:02.027 --> 34:03.469
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

34:03.790 --> 34:05.252
You know, are you the Savior?

34:07.836 --> 34:08.116
Huh?

34:08.216 --> 34:10.880
Let me help all the Christian wives that are here today.

34:12.002 --> 34:16.028
You have the Holy Spirit, but you are not the Holy Spirit.

34:21.035 --> 34:23.179
I know you're trying to bring conviction to that man.

34:23.239 --> 34:23.599
Guess what?

34:23.619 --> 34:25.522
That's not your job.

34:25.890 --> 34:28.033
Your job is to honor and love.

34:28.313 --> 34:30.476
The Holy Spirit is the one who does the convicting.

34:32.498 --> 34:32.899
I don't know.

34:32.919 --> 34:34.360
It's real quiet in this house today.

34:34.461 --> 34:35.101
Hallelujah.

34:36.042 --> 34:36.423
Amen.

34:36.823 --> 34:37.344
Praise the Lord.

34:38.506 --> 34:38.846
Praise the Lord.

34:39.266 --> 34:45.054
So he told them, you know, you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit not many days from now.

34:46.075 --> 34:47.497
And then it's interesting.

34:47.637 --> 34:55.186
They immediately asked him a question that is in Acts chapter one concerning in times.

34:55.362 --> 34:57.585
Were you at this time restored the kingdom Israel?

34:58.746 --> 35:04.993
You know, and in so many words, Jesus said to them, don't focus on that.

35:07.396 --> 35:11.380
He actually said it's not for, you know, the times of the seasons, which the father has placed in his own power.

35:11.600 --> 35:15.725
But I mean, basically he kind of sideswiped that and said, don't worry about that.

35:17.427 --> 35:23.634
Instead, he pointed their attention in another direction in verse eight, but you

35:23.778 --> 35:37.599
we'll receive power, Acts chapter one verse eight, but you will receive power when the Holy Spirit has come upon you and you will be my witnesses in Jerusalem and in all Judea and Samaria and to the ends of the earth.

35:38.500 --> 35:38.861
Amen?

35:39.923 --> 35:52.722
Sure, it's perfectly fine and good to talk about End Times event and to preach on that, but I think some people are so focused on those things on the end that they're ignoring

35:52.866 --> 35:56.129
what's happening right now in the lives of people all around them.

35:58.471 --> 35:59.172
See, here's the thing.

36:00.373 --> 36:05.738
If we preach the gospel to all nations, then the end will come.

36:07.320 --> 36:09.922
It may not fit according to your timeline, but it will come.

36:11.664 --> 36:12.745
Amen.

36:12.765 --> 36:13.366
Praise the Lord.

36:14.667 --> 36:21.874
So he wants us to be his witnesses and he wants those witnesses to be empowered.

36:22.402 --> 36:27.368
You will receive power when the Holy Spirit comes on you when you're clothed with power from on high.

36:28.490 --> 36:31.093
And so that means these thoughts are connected.

36:31.493 --> 36:32.655
You will be my witnesses.

36:33.236 --> 36:41.045
I think personally, the reason some Christians are never filled with the Holy Spirit is they have no interest in being his witness.

36:44.249 --> 36:46.873
See, there's always purpose in God's power.

36:48.094 --> 36:51.058
He doesn't anoint you so you could walk around and feel anointed.

36:52.706 --> 36:56.129
The anointing is not a toy we play with, it's a tool we work with.

36:57.631 --> 37:01.995
I think some people aren't particularly concerned about a lost and dying world around them.

37:02.035 --> 37:04.097
So then you don't need this, do you?

37:06.180 --> 37:06.500
Amen.

37:06.840 --> 37:12.406
On the other hand, I think when you're filled with the Holy Spirit, I think it will deepen your concern for a lost world around you.

37:13.307 --> 37:13.667
Amen.

37:13.687 --> 37:15.569
Maybe some people, maybe that's it.

37:15.809 --> 37:20.594
I think some people have told themselves, well, I'm not really concerned about

37:20.674 --> 37:24.259
the dying world, because I don't feel like there's anything I could do about it.

37:25.120 --> 37:25.901
So that's why.

37:26.642 --> 37:37.876
But when you're empowered by the Holy Spirit, now you've got the tools to do the job, and I think you'll be more enthusiastic and more motivated to be a witness for him.

37:41.781 --> 37:42.942
Now, here's a thought.

37:44.024 --> 37:49.010
These men that he was speaking to in Acts chapter 1, men and women,

37:49.314 --> 37:52.939
they personally accompany Jesus for three and a half years.

37:54.361 --> 37:54.561
Right?

37:55.302 --> 38:00.209
They didn't just read about it in their Bibles or hear about it preached from pulpits.

38:00.890 --> 38:01.691
They were there.

38:03.092 --> 38:05.396
They were eyewitnesses to his miracles.

38:06.237 --> 38:06.417
Right?

38:06.777 --> 38:10.603
They personally saw him crucified.

38:10.943 --> 38:16.130
They were there when he appeared to them with a resurrected, glorified body.

38:16.170 --> 38:16.851
They felt him.

38:16.871 --> 38:17.492
They touched him.

38:17.672 --> 38:19.154
They heard his voice.

38:20.642 --> 38:27.292
Basically, you could say they attended Bible school for three years, the best Bible school in the world.

38:28.273 --> 38:34.182
They didn't have any classrooms, they didn't have any books, but they had only one teacher and he was the son of God and he was the son of God.

38:35.123 --> 38:45.679
And now they've been personally trained, personally trained by Jesus to take his place and continue his ministry after his departure.

38:46.740 --> 38:49.264
Most people would say, that's it?

38:49.444 --> 38:50.546
I mean, what else do you need?

38:51.458 --> 38:56.084
But he said, wait, you're not ready.

38:57.366 --> 39:04.696
See, if these men and women needed the baptism with the Holy Spirit, how much more do we need it?

39:06.078 --> 39:07.199
We need it even more.

39:07.259 --> 39:08.961
Are you out there today?

39:09.041 --> 39:09.843
Praise the Lord.

39:10.403 --> 39:10.844
Amen.

39:10.904 --> 39:16.511
Now, he said, wait until you're clothed with power from on high.

39:16.531 --> 39:20.236
The Greek word for power, of course, is the word dunamis, right?

39:20.557 --> 39:21.458
Like dynamite.

39:22.114 --> 39:33.027
The world has largely, not completely, but by and large, ignored the testimony, the witness of the church.

39:36.050 --> 39:42.798
I'm not saying everybody, but generally speaking, by and large, the world has ignored the church's testimony.

39:44.160 --> 39:46.823
Now, I'm not suggesting you do this.

39:48.025 --> 39:49.266
Please don't do this.

39:49.730 --> 39:57.645
But tomorrow morning, if you walked into your local bank with dynamite taped to your chest, I guarantee you, nobody would ignore you.

40:02.074 --> 40:06.322
Like I said, in case you just woke up, I'm telling you not to do that.

40:06.690 --> 40:19.769
But if you've got dynamite, dunamis, real dynamite, strapped to your chest, I guarantee you, every teller, every patron in the bank, every officer, all of Virginia Beach, you'll be famous.

40:21.051 --> 40:24.956
I can say I knew him when, before he went to jail.

40:27.600 --> 40:34.290
It's because we were trying to do a job without the right equipment.

40:34.786 --> 40:37.690
That means without the Baptist and Holy Spirit, we're not clothed with power.

40:37.890 --> 40:42.096
I think sometimes the demons are laughing at us because we're trying to do the work of Christ and our underwear.

40:45.681 --> 40:46.603
Are you out there today?

40:47.764 --> 40:48.345
Praise the Lord.

40:48.986 --> 40:53.773
So he told them, you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit, not many days from now.

40:54.394 --> 40:57.418
In fact, if you calculate it, they didn't have to wait long.

40:58.860 --> 41:00.242
It was less than 10 days.

41:01.314 --> 41:04.879
It was more like seven days, maybe a little bit less than seven days, you see.

41:05.480 --> 41:10.368
So some people think that you have to wait and wait and wait and wait.

41:10.408 --> 41:12.671
I've been waiting 20 years to be filled with spirit.

41:12.872 --> 41:13.973
Well, if I were you, I'd forget it.

41:14.975 --> 41:17.279
It doesn't take 20 years to be filled with the spirit.

41:17.679 --> 41:18.581
Are you out there today?

41:18.621 --> 41:19.682
Amen.

41:20.183 --> 41:21.305
They didn't have to wait long.

41:21.445 --> 41:25.631
And after the day of Pentecost, nobody was ever told to wait again.

41:25.671 --> 41:29.938
Nobody in the book of Acts ever told anybody, wait.

41:30.338 --> 41:32.140
That is to say, wait to be filled with the Spirit.

41:32.600 --> 41:39.607
Let me just go through this again for the benefit of some who don't know it and maybe just to help you to minister to other people.

41:39.667 --> 41:51.498
Sometimes, see, when I study the scriptures like on the Holy Spirit or on healing or other topics, usually it's not primarily for my benefit, it's so I can help other people.

41:52.840 --> 41:57.945
